A batch extractor for .rar files. In a directory with many .rar files, extract
them all.

usage: anrar [-h] [-d] [-i] [-p PASSWORD] [-v {0,1,2}] [--version]

Extracts all rar files in the current directory

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -d, --delete-files    delete .rar files after succesful extraction (default
                        is to keep them)
  -i, --interactive     enables interactive mode, where unrar queries must be
                        responded to with y/n
  -p PASSWORD, --password PASSWORD
                        the password required to extract files
  -v {0,1,2}, --verbosity {0,1,2}
                        verbosity of output. 0 for silence, 1 for errors only,
                        2 for full output
  --version             show program's version number and exit
